#
# muvm is the Asahi Linux microVM runner — runs
# programs from your system in a microVM using
# libkrun.  Originally developed for the Asahi
# Linux project (Linux on Apple Silicon) to run
# x86_64 binaries via FEX/Box emulators inside
# a virtualized environment.  Authored by the
# AsahiLinux project.  878 GH stars.  Sister
# tools: libkrun (virtualization library it
# depends on), FEX (x86-on-arm64 emulator), Box86
# (x86-on-arm32 emulator), passt (network proxy
# for unprivileged containers).
#
# Critical extraction note: muvm uses **Rust
# `bpaf` library** at cli_options.rs:5 — corpus's
# **first documented bpaf library** + **seventh
# documented Rust CLI library** (joining clap,
# clap-derive, structopt, argh, gumdrop, lexopt
# from previous rounds).  bpaf is pacak/bpaf,
# the COMBINATOR-STYLE Rust CLI parser with
# APPLICATIVE-functor design (inspired by R270
# Haskell optparse-applicative).  Distinct from
# clap (declarative struct-based via derive macro),
# structopt (clap-derive predecessor), argh (Google,
# similar to clap-derive), gumdrop (lighter clap-
# derive alternative), lexopt (tokenizer-only,
# parse-it-yourself).  bpaf's distinguishing
# features: COMBINATOR primitives (`long`,
# `short`, `positional`, `any`) that COMPOSE via
